'''Brejinho''' (''Little Swamp'') is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009, according with [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|IBGE]] was 7.369<ref>http://www.ibge.gov.br/home/estatistica/populacao/estimativa2009/POP2009_DOU.pdf [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|IBGE]] Population 2009 Brejinho, page 32]</ref> and <!--, the density is /km²-->the area is 106.3&nbsp;km².
==Geography==
* State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Sertão]] Pernambucano * Boundaries - [[Paraiba]] state ('''N''' and '''W'''); [[São José do Egito]] and [[Terezinha]] ('''S'''); [[Itapetim]] ('''E'''). * Area - 106.3&nbsp;km² * Elevation - 737 m * Hidrography - [[Pajeú River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[hiperxerófila]] * Clima - [[semi arid]] - hot and dry * Annual average temperature - 22.5 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 410&nbsp;km
==Economy==
The main economic activity in '''Brejinho''' is [[agribusiness]], especially the breeding of [[cattle]], [[goat]]s, [[sheep]], [[pig]]s, [[chickens]]; and planting of [[maize|corn]] and [[beans]].
